	abstract = {The article presents a new edition of V.I. Morosanova's "Self-regulation Profile Questionnaire-SRPQM"-"Self-regulation Profile Questionnaire-SRPQM 2020". This Questionnaire is designed to assess the development of a person's conscious self-regulation and profile of its stylistic features consistently manifested in various types of voluntary activity and life situations. In this new edition, the list of statements has been updated and reduced, and scales revised. There are now 28 statements, comprised of 7 scales (four statements in each scale): Planning goals, modeling significant conditions, programming actions, evaluating results, flexibility, reliability, persistence. In total, the study involved 2087 people of various ages. The SRPQM-2020 has demonstrated good internal consistency and retest reliability. The seven-scale structure of the questionnaire was confirmed by a confirmatory factor analysis. Validity of the methodology was substantiated (as expected) by the statistically significant correlations of its scales with indicators of the basic version of Morosanova's "Self-regulation Profile Questionnaire-SRPQM" (2004), and also by the revealed well-interpreted links with personality dispositions (according to the Big Five model). The results of the questionnaire development were replicated on a large sample of different age respondents. Empirical data was obtained in favor of theoretical ideas about the conscious self-regulation as a controlling meta-level of the psychic self-regulation, including the cognitive-operational and personal-regulatory levels, as well as a higher-order factor-the integrative level of conscious self-regulation, reflecting the general development of a person's subject activity. This article renders the text of the questionnaire, instructions, and keys. © 2020 Rossiiskaya Akademiya Obrazovaniya. All rights reserved.},
